INSIGHTS, FINDINGS AND CONCLUSION.

Phase 4 focuses on interpreting the results from Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and concluding the key observations from the hotel booking dataset.
This phase translates visual trends into meaningful insights that help understand booking behaviors, cancellation patterns, hotel preferences, and demand fluctuations.


1. Key Insights from the Dataset

1.1 Hotel Type & Booking Trends

City Hotel receives more bookings than Resort Hotel.

Higher demand in City Hotel may relate to business travel, urban tourism, and accessibility.


1.2 Cancellation Patterns

A significant share of bookings is canceled, especially when:

Lead time is high

Guests choose Non-Refundable rooms

Market segment = Online TA/Travel Agents

Cancellation rate is strongly influenced by booking behavior and hotel policies.


1.3 Seasonality & Monthly Trends

Bookings peak during summer months (June–August).

Lowest number of bookings appear in winter months.

ADR (Average Daily Rate) also increases during peak seasons.


1.4 Customer Demographics & Guest Composition

Most guests are couples or families.


Majority of bookings originate from:

Portugal

United Kingdom

France

Spain


Most guests arrive with 2–3 total members.


1.5 ADR & Pricing Trends

City Hotels have higher ADR during weekdays.

Resort Hotels show high ADR during vacation seasons.

Higher ADR sometimes correlates with higher cancellations.


1.6 Stay Duration Insights

Long stays are more common in Resort Hotels.

City Hotel stays are usually short (1–2 nights).



2. Business Recommendations

✔ Reduce cancellations

Offer discounts for early confirmation or flexible booking policies.

✔ Improve demand forecasting

Use seasonal booking patterns to optimize pricing and staffing.

✔ Adjust promotional strategies

Focus promotions based on customer geography & peak times.

✔ Revenue optimization

Increase ADR during peak months; offer special packages during low season.



3. Conclusion

The Hotel Booking Demand dataset reveals several important patterns, including the high cancellation rate,seasonality in bookings, varying ADR across hotel types,
and trends across guest demographics. These insights can help hotels improve revenue management, reduce cancellations, and better understand customer behavior.
